body:
Continuation of #4240 , but different issue.

```systemverilog
module t;
    typedef struct {
        struct {
            logic m0;
            logic [3:0] m1;
            logic m2;
        } sub;
    } struct_t;
    struct_t s1;
    struct_t s2;

    assign {s1.sub.m0, s1.sub.m1, s1.sub.m2} = {1'b0, 4'h5, 1'b1};
    assign {s2.sub.m0, s2.sub.m1, s2.sub.m2} = {1'b0, 4'h5, 1'b1};
    
    initial begin
        if(s1.sub != s2.sub) begin
            $fatal();
        end else begin
            $finish();
        end
    end

endmodule
```

Results in:
`verilator_bin  --build --main --binary --cc  test2.sv`

```
Vtest2___024root__DepSet_hef21559d__0__Slow.cpp: In function ‘void Vtest2___024root___eval_initial__TOP(Vtest2___024root*)’:
Vtest2___024root__DepSet_hef21559d__0__Slow.cpp:22:26: error: no match for ‘operator&’ (operand types are ‘unsigned int’ and ‘Vtest2___struct4’)
   22 |     if (VL_UNLIKELY(((1U & vlSelf->t__DOT__s1.__PVT__sub)
      |                       ~~ ^ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      |                       |                       |
      |                       unsigned int            Vtest2___struct4
/tools/work/SoCMake-Ibex/deps/_deps/verisc/open/verilator-106965270/share/verilator/include/verilatedos.h:66:45: note: in definition of macro ‘VL_UNLIKELY’
   66 | # define VL_UNLIKELY(x) __builtin_expect(!!(x), 0)  // Prefer over C++20 [[unlikely]]
      |                                             ^
Vtest2___024root__DepSet_hef21559d__0__Slow.cpp:23:29: error: no match for ‘operator&’ (operand types are ‘unsigned int’ and ‘Vtest2___struct4’)
   23 |                      != (1U & vlSelf->t__DOT__s2.__PVT__sub)))) {
      |                          ~~ ^ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      |                          |                       |
      |                          unsigned int            Vtest2___struct4
/tools/work/SoCMake-Ibex/deps/_deps/verisc/open/verilator-106965270/share/verilator/include/verilatedos.h:66:45: note: in definition of macro ‘VL_UNLIKELY’
```

The error is in 1U & struct, this bitwise should be removed in case of structure comparison.
I am not sure why is it there in the first place?

I can proceed to remove the bitwise & for the case of struct if that is what needs to be done?
